The paper deals with machine learning and graph theory, specifically focusing on the vulnerability of vertex classification to adversarial attacks. This suggests that the paper is likely to fall under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the impact of topological characteristics of graphs on the success of adversarial attacks, which could place it under the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes defenses against these attacks, which could place it under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
